title: Letter between Frederic Engel and Donald Crabtree
creator: Crabtree, Donald "Don" E.
description: Letter to Frederic Engel noting that Crabtree cannot make any commitments to visit due to Earl Swanson's recent passing. Crabtree is sending some film titles and a paper that would be useful to Engel and his students. He analyzes the flakes Engel sent, noting their flaking qualities.
subject: flintknapping; flaking; visit; lithic technology; lithic technology; article exchange; artifact identification; professional correspondence
source: Donald E. Crabtree Lithic Comparative Collection

title: Letter to Donald and Evelyn Crabtree from Jeff Flenniken
creator: Flenniken, John "Jeff" J.
description: Letter thanking the Crabtrees for hosting Flenniken's visit. He enjoyed flintknapping and was able to collect more rock material for future use on the drive home.
subject: personal correspondence; travel; visit; flintknapping; experimental archaeology; lithic technology; material sourcing
source: Donald E. Crabtree Lithic Comparative Collection

title: Ce.6523
creator: Indigenous
description: This was made by an unknown Indigenous creator and was used as a flintknapping example for Donald E. Crabtree. Dr. Robert Lee Sappington points out that many of the items made by Crabtree bare a strong resemblance to this artifact.
subject: experimental artifacts; lithics
